#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/community/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Community"
msgstr "Bendruomenė"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Whether it be to solve a problem or to contribute in any way, the Xfce communities are a good place to get help or to share your ideas. You might also want to have a look at the communities of the different distributions which provide Xfce.\n"
msgstr "Ar norite gauti pagalbos ar kaipnors prisidėti, Xfce bendruomenės yra gera vieta pradėti. Taipogi jums gali būti įdomu peržiūrėti skirtingų distributyvų Xfce bendruomenes.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mailing lists"
msgstr "Pašto konferencijos"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Almost all development and coordination work is taking place on the Xfce mailing lists. A summary of all lists is available at [mail.xfce.org](https://mail.xfce.org). There is also a user-specific list where you can ask questions and freely discuss about the desktop.\n"
msgstr "Beveik visas kūrimo ir koordinavimo darbas atliekamas Xfce pašto konferencijose. Visų laiškų santrauka prieinama [mail.xfce.org](https://mail.xfce.org). Taipogi yra naudotojams skirta konferencija kurioje galite užduoti klausimą ar laisvai diskutuoti apie darbalaukį.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "**NOTE:** In order to post to these lists, you must first subscribe.\n"
msgstr "**PASTABA**: norėdami rašyti šiose konferencijose, pirmiausia turite prisijungti.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Matrix"
msgstr "„Matrix“"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have a problem that you cannot resolve, you might want to try asking a question in our Matrix channel [#xfce](https://matrix.to/#/#xfce:matrix.org). The channel has several active users. It is recommended that you consult the [documentation](https://docs.xfce.org/) about your problem before asking your question.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Forums"
msgstr "Forumai"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "For users who prefer forums, the [Xfce Forum](https://forum.xfce.org/) is the place to be. Active contributors will be able to help you, but please do not use it for bug reports.\n"
msgstr "Naudotojams kuriems labiau patinka forumai, yra skirtas [Xfce forumas](https://forum.xfce.org/). Aktyvūs bendraautoriai jums padės, tačiau nenaudokite forumo pranešimams apie klaidas.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Social Networks"
msgstr "Socialiniai tinklai"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can follow us on the official [Mastodon account](https://floss.social/@xfce) or [Twitter account](https://twitter.com/xfceofficial)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "About"
msgstr "Apie"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce is a lightweight desktop environment for UNIX-like operating systems. It aims to be fast and low on system resources, while still being visually appealing and user friendly.\n"
msgstr "Xfce yra supaprastinta darbalaukio aplinka, skirta Unix tipo sistemoms. Ji stengiasi būti greita ir naudoti kuo mažiau sistemos išteklių, tuo pačiu išlaikant patogumą naudotojui ir malonią išvaizdą.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce embodies the traditional UNIX philosophy of modularity and re-usability. It consists of a number of components that provide the full functionality one can expect of a modern desktop environment. They are packaged separately and you can pick among the available packages to create the optimal personal working environment.\n"
msgstr "Xfce įkūnija tradicinę lankstumo ir pakartotinio naudojimo UNIX filosofiją. Ją sudaro daug komponentų, kurių visuma suteikia tokį funkcionalumą kokio tikimasi iš šiuolaikinės darbalaukio aplinkos. Komponentai supakuoti atskirai, todėl galite pasirinkti iš daugelio paketų ir susikurti sau optimalią darbalaukio aplinką.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Another priority of Xfce is adherence to standards, specifically those defined at [freedesktop.org](https://freedesktop.org).\n"
msgstr "Kitas Xfce prioritetas yra atitikimas standartams, ypatingai tiems, kurie yra aprašyti [freedesktop.org](https://freedesktop.org).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce can be installed on several UNIX platforms. It is known to compile on Linux, NetBSD, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, Cygwin and MacOS X, on x86, PPC, Sparc, Alpha...\n"
msgstr "Xfce gali būti įdiegta keliose UNIX platformose. Yra žinoma jog susikompiliuoja ant Linux, NetBSD, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, Cygwin ir MacOS X, ant x86, PPC, Sparc, Alpha...\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/_index.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Features"
msgstr "Galimybės"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce contains a number of core components for the minimum tasks you'd expect from a desktop environment:\n"
msgstr "Xfce turi daug pagrindinių komponentų kurių tikitės iš darbalaukio aplinkos:\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/_index.md:18 content/about/tour44.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Window Manager"
msgstr "Langų tvarkytuvė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manages the placement of windows on the screen, provides window decorations and manages workspaces or virtual desktops.\n"
msgstr "Tvarko langų išdėstymą ekrane, suteikia langų dekoracijas ir tvarko darbo sritis ar virtualius darbalaukius.\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Desktop Manager"
msgstr "Darbalaukio tvarkytuvė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sets the background image and provides a root window menu, desktop icons or minimized icons and a windows list.\n"
msgstr "Nustato fono paveikslą ir pateikia pagrindinį lango meniu, darbalaukio piktogramas ar suskleistas piktogramas ir langų sąrašą.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/_index.md:26 content/about/tour44.md:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "Panel"
msgstr "Skydelis"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switch between opened windows, launch applications, switch workspaces and menu plugins to browse applications or directories.\n"
msgstr "Persijunkite tarp atvertų langų, paleistų programų, perjunkite darbo sritis ir meniu įskiepius, naršykite programas ar katalogus.\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Session Manager"
msgstr "Seansų tvarkytuvė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Controls the login and power management of the desktop and allows you to store multiple login sessions.\n"
msgstr "Valdo darbalaukio prisijungimą ir maitinimo tvarkymą, taipogi leidžia įrašyti kelis prisijungimo seansus.\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Application Finder"
msgstr "Programų ieškyklė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shows the applications installed on your system in categories, so you can quickly find and launch them.\n"
msgstr "Rodo jūsų sistemoje įdiegtas programas kategorijomis, taigi galite greitai jas rasti ir vykdyti.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/_index.md:38 content/about/tour44.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "File Manager"
msgstr "Failų tvarkytuvė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Provides the basic file-management features and unique utilities like the bulk renamer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:42 content/about/tour410.md:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "Settings Manager"
msgstr "Nustatymų tvarkytuvė"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tools to control the various settings of the desktop; like keyboard shortcuts, appearance, display settings, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "Beside the basic set of modules, Xfce also provides numerous additional applications and plugins so you can extend your desktop the way you like, for example a terminal emulator, text editor, sound mixer, application finder, image viewer, iCal based calendar and a CD and DVD burning application. You can read more about the modules of Xfce in the [projects](/projects) page.\n"
msgstr "Be pagrindinių modulių rinkinio, Xfce taipogi suteikia daug papildomų programų ir įskiepių, todėl galite išplėsti savo darbalaukio galimybes taip kaip norite, pvz. terminalo emuliatoriumi, tekstiniu redaktoriumi, garso maišikliu, programų ieškykle, paveikslų žiūrykle, iCal paremtu kalendoriumi ir CD/DVD įrašymo programa. Daugiau apie Xfce modulius galite paskaityti [projektų](/projects) puslapyje.\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Get Involved"
msgstr "Prisidėkite"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Welcome to the Xfce community. By joining our team, you will be part of an international effort by hundreds of people working to deliver a stunning Free Software computing experience. You will meet new friends, learn new skills and make a difference to millions of users while working with people from all around the globe. There are many different ways you can become part of this, just read on and pick an area which interests you or seems challenging.\n"
msgstr "Sveiki atvykę į Xfce bendruomenę. Prisijungę prie mūsų komandos, jūs prisidėsite prie šimtų žmonių pastangų padaryti nemokamos programinės įrangos pasaulį geresniu. Sutiksite naujų draugų, išmoksite naujų dalykų ir padarysite milijonų žmonių gyvenimą geresniu. Yra daug būdų tapti dalimi, skaitykite ir pasirinkite sritį kuri jums įdomi. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Possible tasks include testing, bug reporting; writing code, developing artwork, documentation or translations; or spreading the word and helping out with promotion and marketing both on line and at tradeshows and conferences.\n"
msgstr "Galimos užduotys įtraukia testavimą, pranešimą apie klaidas; kodo rašymą, meninio apipavidalinamo kūrimą, dokumentavimą ar vertimą; ar žodžio apie Xfce skleidimą.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Documentation"
msgstr "Dokumentacija"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "There's lots of people using and testing Xfce. By providing useful and up-to-date documentation, you will make a big impact on helping people understand how to make the most of the Xfce Desktop Environment. [Learn More →](https://docs.xfce.org/contribute/documentation)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Translation"
msgstr "Vertimas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Are you fluent in multiple languages? By contributing your translations of text to the Xfce Desktop Environment, you will help Xfce be a better part of the global market and more accessible to the millions of potential users out there. [Learn More →](https://docs.xfce.org/contribute/translate/start)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Development"
msgstr "Kūrimas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "By becoming a developer, you can make a big difference while enjoying a challenging and fun experience. You'll learn to be a better coder, you will get to implement new features and defeat daunting bugs, creating a stunning product, all the while collaborating with people from all around the world. You can start by browsing the [source code](https://gitlab.xfce.org).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Promotion"
msgstr "Propagavimas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you own a blog or website you can greatly help by spreading the word and encouraging new users to give Xfce a try. If you have a Mastodon or Twitter account you can also help by reposting any announcements we make to help us reach a larger audience.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bug Reporting and testing"
msgstr "Pranešimas apie klaidas ir testavimas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "One of the most useful tasks that we rely on the community for is testing and reporting of bugs. Since Xfce runs on various platform and in a lot of different setups, testing all changes in every possible situation is an impossible task. As such we kindly ask users to assist in testing, and reporting all bugs they may find, using our [bug tracker](https://gitlab.xfce.org).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once a bug has been found, the cause of the bug needs to be tracked down, and then (obviously) fixed. If you want to get involved in the actual development process of Xfce a great way to start is by solving bugs and then submitting a patch file.\n"
msgstr "Kai klaida rasta, reikia nustatyti klaidos priežastį ir tada ištaisyti. Jei norite prisidėti prie tikrojo kūrimo proceso, puiki pradžia yra klaidų sprendimas, taisymas ir pataisų kūrimas.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "OpenCollective"
msgstr "„OpenCollective“"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you want to fund the project, you can use OpenCollective. Xfce has created two collectives, known as [Xfce ($)](https://opencollective.com/xfce) and [Xfce-Eu (€)](https://opencollective.com/xfce-eu) respectively. [Learn More →](https://mail.xfce.org/pipermail/xfce/2021-May/037348.html)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/tour420.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.20 tour"
msgstr "Xfce 4.20 turas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:8
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "This tour will introduce you to new major features of Xfce 4.16. It only covers improvements made on the (user-visible) surface; for the full list of changes, see the [changelog](/download/changelogs/4.16/).\n"
msgid "This tour will introduce you to new major features of Xfce 4.20. It only covers improvements made on the (user-visible) surface.\n"
msgstr "Šis turas supažindins jus su naujomis, pagrindinėmis Xfce 4.16 laidos ypatybėmis. Jame aprašomi tik išoriniai (naudotojui matomi) atlikti pakeitimai. Pilnam pakeitimų sąrašui, žiūrėkite [keitinių žurnalą](/download/changelogs/4.16/).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check the full [Xfce 4.20 changelog](/download/changelogs/4.20/) for a detailed list of changes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:11 content/about/tour420.md:204
#: content/about/tour418.md:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wayland"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Important Notice:** Please be aware that the Wayland support in Xfce 4.20 is experimental. It is recommended for advanced users only, as you may encounter bugs and experience incomplete functionality. Proceed with caution!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Thanks to [Brian](https://gitlab.xfce.org/kelnos) and [Gaël](https://gitlab.xfce.org/Tamaranch) almost all Xfce components are able to run on Wayland windowing, while still keeping support for X11 windowing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "This major effort was achieved by abstracting away any X11/Wayland windowing specific calls and making use of Wayland/Wlroots protocols. A whole new Xfce library, \"libxfce4windowing\" was introduced during that process. XWayland will not be required to run any of the ported Xfce components.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "So far Xfce does not feature a compositor which supports Wayland. If you want to run Xfce in Wayland, Labwc and Wayfire will give you the best results. A detailed instruction on this can be found [here](https://wiki.xfce.org/releng/wayland_roadmap#testing). Please be aware that Wayland support is still experimental!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Plans are underway to add Wayland support to Xfwm4 while preserving its existing X11 functionality. However, such a restructurization will be a major effort and we cannot tell yet when/if it will be done, so please don't hold your breath waiting for it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "For few components and multiple features, it was not possible to port them to Wayland, partly because there are no standardized Wayland protocols available yet to provide the required services:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Workspace support is missing (ext-workspace protocol [was just merged](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/wayland/wayland-protocols/-/merge_requests/40)).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Systray icons will be missing for multiple applications (required to use StatusNotifier instead of GtkStatusIcon)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce4-settings: Keyboard and mouse settings so far are internal to the Wayland compositor and as such the according Xfce dialogs won't be available on Wayland yet.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Power related keyboard handling (brightness keys, suspend, etc.) is internal to the Wayland compositor and as such cannot be supported yet by Xfce components.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wayland does not specify a native protocol for taking screenshots. However, xfce4-screenshooter already supports screenshots via the wlroots 'screencopy' protocol (entire screen). Screenshots of a rectangle selection or the active window are not yet supported via Wayland.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Some other Xfce components don't run at all on Wayland:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfwm4\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfdashboard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce4-screensaver (porting to Wayland [completed but not merged](https://gitlab.xfce.org/apps/xfce4-screensaver/-/merge_requests/28), as it requires the experimental [libwlembed library](https://gitlab.xfce.org/kelnos/libwlembed))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce4-windowck-plugin (needs to be [ported to libxfce4windowing](https://gitlab.xfce.org/panel-plugins/xfce4-windowck-plugin/-/issues/37))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce4-xkb-plugin (keyboard handling is internal to the Wayland compositor)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "More detailed info on the current Wayland status can be found on our [Wayland roadmap.](https://wiki.xfce.org/releng/wayland_roadmap)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:43 content/about/tour418.md:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scaling"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icons and thumbnail scaling was fixed for various components. Various missing icons for larger scales were added. Any blurriness when using Xfce components on a HiDPI display should be gone now.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "[exo](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/exo/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icon View Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "By using different container types, the \"Exo-Icon-View\" now can handle 100,000 files and more without freezing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "Type ahead search box"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "The type ahead search box in the exo icon view now always stays inside the according view widget.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "[libxfce4ui](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/libxfce4ui/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shortcut Editor"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shortcuts now can be used for multiple actions if they don't conflict with each other.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "About Dialog"
msgstr "„Apie“ dialogas"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "The dialog now shows the distribution logo, information about the used windowing system and the used GPU.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "![libxfce4ui - about dialog][img-libxfce4ui_about]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "[libxfce4windowing](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/libxfce4windowing/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "This library is new to Xfce. Libxfce4windowing is an abstraction library that attempts to present windowing concepts (screens, top level windows, workspaces, etc.) in a windowing-system-independent manner.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Currently, X11 is fully supported via libwnck. Wayland is partially supported by using various Wayland protocol extensions. However, the full range of operations available on X11 is not available on Wayland, due to missing features in these protocols extensions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "[thunar](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounted and Remote Locations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mount points now show an emblem and have a specific type description.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ipv6 remote URLs are now supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to create symbolic links as well on remote locations.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "Search"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is not required any more to wait until a search is finished to open the context menu on search results.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:89 content/about/tour418.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Toolbar"
msgstr "Įrankių juosta"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "A couple of new toolbar buttons were added:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "View Switcher - A drop-down button to select a view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "Menu - This hamburger button will show automatically in the toolbar, when the menubar is hidden. It will reveal a vertical menu, bar, when pressed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Tab - Open a new tab using the current directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/tour420.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Window - Open a new window using the current directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - new toolbar buttons][img-thunar_toolbar_new_items]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - improved hamburger toolbar button][img-thunar_toolbar_hamburger]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "On shrinking the Thunar window, toolbar items will now be moved to an overflow menu. Like that, it is possible to maintain smaller thunar windows.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "Furthermore, a bug was fixed which prevented the usage of submenu custom actions in the toolbar.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Window Decorations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is now an option to use client side decorations in Thunar (CSD).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - CSD with menu][img-thunar_csd_with_menu]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - CSD without menu][img-thunar_csd_without_menu]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:114 content/about/tour418.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "Statusbar"
msgstr "Būsenos juosta"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "An option to show the number of hidden files in the statusbar was added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Recently Used Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Only files which were successfully opened are now added to the list of recently used files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "Directories won't be added to the recently used files anymore.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "Symbolic Icons"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is now an option to use symbolic icons in the side pane and colored icons in the toolbar.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - symbolic icons][img-thunar_symbolic_icons]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - colored icons][img-thunar_colored_icons]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "Drag and Drop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "While dragging files, folders are now opened automatically on hover.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "While dragging files, the focus of the split view pane is now updated when hovered.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the past, you might have faced situation involving bigger numbers of files in which thunar showed a freeze. Due to various different performance measures, thunar now is much more bullet-proof for action involving huge numbers of files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "This was achieved by using appropriate container types, moving some actions into separate jobs and throttling of view-updates.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "A [number of integration test cases](https://wiki.xfce.org/thunar/dev/integration_testcases) will be used in order to keep performance on the current level in the future.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:146 content/about/tour418.md:171
#, no-wrap
msgid "Custom Actions"
msgstr "Tinkinti veiksmai"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shortcuts for custom action will now as well work when the custom action is located in a sub-menu.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "File Transfer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "For file validation in thunar 4.18.x a md5 checksum was calculated for source and target file. This calculation turned out to be rather slow and actually superfluous. Now files are just compared directly. In addition, the usage of direct I/O operations now attempts to prevent comparison of possibly cached buffers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "An option was added to only copy files in parallel if the relevant devices are in idle state. This prevents possible fragmentation during copy for HDD drives.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Transferring files no longer steals the current focus.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "The file transfer question dialog now provides the same options while having less buttons. In addition, file thumbnails now are properly requested by the dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - file transfer dialog][img-thunar_transfer_dialog]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:162
#, no-wrap
msgid "Launchers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "By default, launcher names instead of filenames are shown now for trusted launchers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Undo/Redo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "The user now will be asked before any deletion will be done by an undo operation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:170 content/about/tour418.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "List View"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Similar to the tree-view side pane, the main view now also supports folder expansion.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - expandable folders][img-thunar_expandable_folders]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:176 content/about/tour418.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Split View"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "A shortcut now can be used to toggle between split-view panes, and the focused pane now uses different coloring.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "![thunar - split view][img-thunar_split_view]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "A dialog will now ask for confirmation when closing a split-pane with multiple tabs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfce4-appfinder](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-appfinder/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "The application list now as well can be navigated via Ctrl+N / Ctrl+P keys (VI default).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "An option was added to close the Appfinder window automatically when focus is lost.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ctrl+Enter can be used to execute commands immediately when selecting entries from the dropdown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "Within the new version, application specific actions will show on right click.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "An option to show generic names of launchers was added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "Appfinder optionally can now be launched as a daemon, so that it will respond even quicker.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "An option allows now to launch items on a single click.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-appfinder - settings][img-appfinder_new]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfce4-panel](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-panel/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "The border width of the panel is now configurable.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "For manual installations: the panel now does its best to find plugins in XDG base directories, and better preserves its configuration when it can't find them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clock"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "LCD clock: An option was added to visualize inactive segments.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Analog: There is now an optional 24h mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "Digital: Week numbers now are shown optionally.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "Show Desktop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is now the possibility to show the desktop when hovering the mouse on the \"show desktop\" panel icon.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tasklist"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icon size management has been improved overall, notably by switching to libxfce4windowing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:226 content/about/tour420.md:354
#: content/about/tour418.md:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preferences"
msgstr "Nuostatos"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "The 'delete' key can now be used to remove panel objects, and several objects can be removed at once.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "Panel objects in the panel configuration list now will have the same icons as in the panel itself.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-panel - panel configuration list][img-panel_item_list]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfce4-power-manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-power-manager/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "Screen Locking"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:239
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is no dedicated \"security\" tab anymore. Lock screen management was massively simplified and \"Light Locker\" was dropped. \"lock-on-sleep\" is now synchronized with xfce4-session and xfce4-screensaver.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "Screen locking settings are now only handled by xfce4-screensaver to avoid conflicts. A button to open xfce4-screensaver-preferences was added:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-power-manager - settings][img-power_manager_settings]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:245
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-screensaver - settings][img-power_manager_screensaver]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:246
#, no-wrap
msgid "Power Settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:249
#, no-wrap
msgid "Support for handling different power profiles via power-profiles-daemon was added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "The overall charge state calculation was wrong for some cases and is now fixed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "When the critical power dialog pops up, unintentional user actions are now prevented.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:255
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is now support for the hybrid sleep mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:257
#, no-wrap
msgid "The device details tab now as well shows the energy rate.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "Others"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:261
#, no-wrap
msgid "Several use-cases for lid close were fixed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:263
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are now the options \"shutdown\" and \"do nothing\" on lid close.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:265
#, no-wrap
msgid "Buttons to change the brightness exponentially and keyboard backlight toggle keys now are supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfce4-session](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-session/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:269
#, no-wrap
msgid "The logout dialog will not provide a checkbox to enable session saving anymore.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:271
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to start a Wayland session via `startxfce4 --wayland`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:273
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimal support for xdg-desktop-portal was added by registering for a wallpaper, screenshot and background xapp.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfce4-settings](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:276 content/about/tour418.md:65
#: content/about/tour412.md:73 content/about/tour410.md:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "Appearance Settings"
msgstr "Išvaizdos nustatymai"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icon themes are now loaded in a separate thread, in order to prevent a possible freeze.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:281
#, no-wrap
msgid "For icon themes which are known to be incomplete, a warning now will be shown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:283
#, no-wrap
msgid "The usage of client side decorations is opt-in now, not opt-out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:285
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dark themes now are identified and supported in a more reliable way. (Relevant e.g. for the Qogir and Orchis themes)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:286 content/about/tour418.md:59
#: content/about/tour412.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Display Settings"
msgstr "Ekrano nustatymai"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "The default display profile has been added to the list of profiles that can match, and will be used if more than one matches now.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:291
#, no-wrap
msgid "Profile management has been extended to all profiles, not just those that match, and their names can now be edited.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scaling now always is done for both dimensions, and the preview shows the resulting size.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:295
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mirror state management has been improved overall, in particular by removing the need to match refresh rates.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:297
#, no-wrap
msgid "The minimal dialog has been improved, in particular by allowing the display to be extended to the left and from top to bottom, and with compact profile display.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-settings - minimal display][img-settings_display]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mouse Settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "A checkbox was added to toggle between adaptive and flat mouse accel profile.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:305
#, no-wrap
msgid "High resolution scrolling can now be enabled for mice which do support it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:307
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfce4-settings - mouse][img-settings_mouse]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mime Settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to select/change multiple items at once.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:312
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfconf](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfconf/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "A systemd user unit, corresponding to the D-Bus session service, is now added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Whitespaces are now properly escaped when writing a xfconf channel to disk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:319
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfconf-query now displays array contents.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:320
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfdesktop](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfdesktop/start)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:322
#, no-wrap
msgid "Background Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "For random wallpaper cycling, wallpapers now are only repeated after all other wallpapers were shown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:327
#, no-wrap
msgid "Old Xfce backgrounds were ported from .png to .svg to be usable for large screens.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gradients will now be rendered in a gamma-correct way.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icon grid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:333
#, no-wrap
msgid "The confirmation dialog for arranging desktop icons now is optional.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to set custom colors for icon labels and icon background.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:337
#, no-wrap
msgid "The icon grid on each monitor is now independent of one another.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:338
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimized Application Icons"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:341
#, no-wrap
msgid "Window icons are now initially shown on the monitor where the window was present before being minimized.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:343
#, no-wrap
msgid "The context menu (when clicking on an empty space) now has more useful options than before.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "File Icons"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:347
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is now an option to sort folders before files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:349
#, no-wrap
msgid "The positions of the icons are now saved in a way that should avoid icons moving around in unexpected ways when monitors are added and removed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:351
#, no-wrap
msgid "New files and dropped files now will be placed near the current cursor location.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "Icons of fixed disks and drives can now be optionally shown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "The 'Desktop Icons' tab was fully reworked.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfdesktop - settings - desktop icons][img-xfdesktop_settings_icons]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:361
#, no-wrap
msgid "All shortcuts of Xfdesktop now can be configured, using the XfceShortcutsManagers widget.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "![xfdesktop - settings - keyboard shortcuts][img-xfdesktop_settings_shortcuts]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:365
#, no-wrap
msgid "More folders that hold background images were added as shortcuts in the settings dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:367
#, no-wrap
msgid "The settings dialog will update if the background is changed from outside the dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wallpaper image folders now are loaded fully asynchronously to prevent lag.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour420.md:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "Context Menu"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:373
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cascading custom actions will now as well shown correctly in Xfdesktop.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to open multiple selected folders at once.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:377
#, no-wrap
msgid "The context menu now opens on button press rather than button release, as most users will expect.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour420.md:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "The middle-click window list menu has new styling and added features.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour420.md:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "[xfwm4](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfwm4/start)"
